            <h3>Interview with HEMA’s employees</h3>
            <p>
                    In a discussion with one of HEMA’s employees, our group picked up on some areas which we could work on.<br/>
                    First, the store was getting more popular amongst local chinese for its seafood cuisine. An increase in awareness of Hema’s brand could lead to even more customers coming to its store. Without dealing with this issue, the future experience of customers might not be as favourable. Hence, we wanted to improve on the store’s payment process.<br/>
                    Second, greater numbers of visitors to the physical store are not translating into greater amounts of online sales. Customers might be unaware of Hema’s online presence and treat it as another restaurant concept. The creation of a mobile application that is meant to be used both in the store and outside could help to bridge the gap between the online and offline environment.
