        <div class="paragraph">
                <h3>Concept Value</h3>
                <p>
                        At the core of our concept, there is a drive by the need to increase online sales through the improvement of the offline store experience. HEMA’s physical stores are popular amongst young-crowds mainly for the fresh seafood. Our objective is to link users to the online application while in the physical store.<br/>
                        <br/>
                        Usage of our online application within the store does two things:<br/>
                        <b>1. Familarity</b><br/>
                        Users are encouraged to use the online application even when they are not physically at the store as they are more familiar with it.<br/>
                        <b>2. Trust</b><br/>
                        Users are more trusting of the quality of HEMA’s products even when online since the connection to viewing products online within the store, where they currently trust the quality, is triggered.
                </p> 
                <div class="image-middle-container">
                        <img src="/images/hema/10.png" width="50%" margin="50px 50px">
                </div> 
                <p>
                        To improve the offline–online experience, our concept involves 3 strategies:<br/>
                        First, an application is created which allows users to pay in the store without needing to check-out at a physical counter. This improves the seamlessness of the in-store experience, addressing the issue of crowdedness. In addition, it conditions users to make payments through our app. This means that there is less inertia to using our application even when they are at home.<br/>
                        Second, our application will track our users’ product history and movement throughout the store. From this, we will be better able to determine our users’ preferences for certain foods as a form of data collection. We can then tailor future recommendations towards a specific user, thereby further improving their experience at HEMA through personalization and tailoring.<br/>
                        Third, our application will be equipped with image recognition technology that allows it to recognize Hema’s products. Users will be able to determine the nutritional information of categories of food within the store. On top of that, details such as the place of origin of the food can be displayed to the consumer. Again, this helps to improve the overall experience of the physical store.
                </p>   
