                    As can be seen under our revenue streams, the sale of seafood forms a small part of the profits. A greater influence on the bottom line can be attributed to the sale of complementary ingredients to the sale of seafood. This is a good validation for us to focus on the ease with which consumers should be able to buy the accompanying ingredients for their selected choice of seafood.<br/>
                    A big part of our costs can be mitigated through our partnership with Alibaba, such as big data analysis and application development. However, HEMA would still have to spend money on the redesigning their store layout to make it more suitable for coherent use with our online application (removing cashier counters, for example).<br/>
