                    <h3>Persuasive Design Principles</h3>
                    <p>
                            As our main design innovation revolves around the mobile application, our group has tried to implement as many persuasive principles into the user interface design as possible.<br/>
                            Such principles include:<br/>
                            1. Tailoring & Personalisation of recipes. Based on the users’ movements through the store while using the application, we can track what categories of food products they would tend to move towards.<br/>
                            2. Suggestion. An understanding of a user’s taste will allow us to create recommendations of food products to buy. <br/>
                            3. Reduction. Instead of carrying their food products to the cashier to check out, our mobile application allows for users to purchase their products immediately with the shake of their phone screen. This makes things easier than going through the multi-step process of typical online purchases.<br/>
                    </p>
