        <div class="paragraph">
            <h3>Improvements to Process</h3>
            <p>
                    Our orginial concept involved using real-time pictures of Hema’s products to consumers as a display of quality. This concept was based on the idea that our users determined the freshness of the goods by the color of the leaves and the fruit. This meant that the physical appearance of the product had a big role in influencing our consumers’ decisions.<br/>
                    Also, we wanted to create simple but inspiring recipes to our target market group who we believed had sub-optimal cooking skills. This is because the practice of cooking amongst the younger generations of chinese tend to be less prevalent.<br/>
                    After taking into consideration HEMA’s approach, we made significant changes to our final concept. In essence, we have improved on the ways in which we can create tailored recipe recommendations to improve the experience of Hema’s brand. In addition, we found an effective method which can create more offline-online convertions while also reducing overcrowding at Hema’s stores.
            </p>

